  "prompt": "Does IIM Indore select 1 year dropouts for IPM?",
  "response": "Yes, IIM Indore does consider candidates who have taken a gap year for its Integrated Programme in Management (IPM). The selection process for IPM at IIM Indore is quite competitive and holistic, taking into account various factors. Here\u2019s a brief overview of the eligibility criteria and selection process:\n\n### Eligibility Criteria:\n1. **Age**: Candidates should have been born on or after August 1, 2004 (for the 2023 batch).\n2. **Qualification**: Candidates need to have passed the Class XII or equivalent examination in 2022 or 2023.\n3. **Minimum Marks**: A minimum of 60% in the standard X/SSC and standard XII/HSC or equivalent examinations (55% for candidates from SC/ST/PwD category).\n\n### Selection Process:\n1. **IPM Aptitude Test (IPMAT)**: Candidates need to appear for the IPMAT, which is specifically designed for this program.\n2. **Shortlisting**: Based on the IPMAT scores, candidates are shortlisted for the next rounds.\n3. **Written Ability Test (WAT) and Personal Interview (PI)**: Shortlisted candidates undergo WAT and PI.\n4. **Final Selection**: The final selection is based on a composite score considering the candidate\u2019s performance in IPMAT, WAT, PI, and their academic records.\n\nHaving a gap year does not disqualify a candidate, but they must meet the age and academic criteria. It's important for candidates to use their gap year productively, perhaps by engaging in relevant work experience, internships, or skill development activities, as these can be discussed during the PI and may positively impact their application.\n\nFor the most accurate and updated information, it\u2019s always a good idea to check the official IIM Indore website or contact their admissions office directly.",
